{
  "texts": [
    "Their results showed improved accuracy by incorporating both RDMs and angles, surpassing a recurrent neural network (RNN)-based baseline performance while being computationally efficient.The existing solutions, including ANNs and sparse SNNs, typically depend on the conventional radar preprocessing chain to extract range, Doppler, or angular information as the initial step in the network input procedure.",
    "Nevertheless, this preprocessing chain is computationally expensive and introduces substantial complexity.",
    "The solution proposed in [20] addresses these challenges using only raw time-domain radar data with simplified processing.",
    "They skip the 2D FFTs for RDMs and emulate DFT operations in the initial layer of their SNN network.",
    "Also, they exclude Doppler information and angular data, achieving 98.1% accuracy in distinguishing four self-recorded gestures."
  ]
}